         <abstract id="aspace_f152674c21c33fc1faa16f9971ec9804">The collection contains photographs and ephemera produced and collected by Claude Barnett and Etta Moten Barnett during their trips to various countries in Africa, including Ghana, Sierra Leone, Liberia, and Swaziland (later Eswatini).  Also present are photographs of Africa and other locations the Barnetts collected on their trips and in the course of Claude's work with the Associated Negro Press.  Most of the collected photographs were produced by the British Information Services and Central Office of Information.  Collected photographs depict daily life and colonial administration in Nigeria, Sierra Leone, Ghana, Kenya, Togoland (later Togo and Ghana), Jamaica, and other unidentified locations.</abstract>
